Wash and dry produce.

Halve @Ciabatta Bread{2%unit}; toast until golden if desired in a #toaster{}. Thinly slice @Mozzarella Cheese{4%ounce} into 4 rounds.

In a #medium bowl{}, toss @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} and @Balsamic Vinegar{5%teaspoon} to taste. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Spread @Fig Jam{2%ounce} onto cut sides of ciabattas. Fill with @Prosciutto{2%ounce}, mozzarella, and a bit of salad.

Cut sandwiches on a diagonal if desired. Serve with remaining salad on the side.

> There is nothing better than a really great sandwich that takes less than 10 minutes to prepare!

> This Really Great Sandwich has crusty bread, sweet fig jam, salty prosciutto, and creamy fresh mozzarella.